comments: Schroder (OKC) makes marginal contact with Simmons (PHI) in the post that does not affect his SQBR.
Harris (PHI) moves A->B into Grant (OKC) during his jump shot attempt.
Schroder (OKC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Butler's (PHI) drive to the basket.
Redick (PHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Ferguson's (OKC) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Westbrook (OKC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Butler (PHI) maintains his pivot foot after he picks up his dribble.
Simmons (PHI) initiates contact with Westbrook (OKC) that pulls his right hand off of the ball as he attempts to start his dribble, affecting his SQBR.
Westbrook (OKC) turns his body slightly into Butler's (PHI) at the end of the drive, but contact is marginal and does not affect Butler's ability to pass.
[Observable in enhanced video] Ferguson (OKC) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Morris (OKC) seals Scott (PHI) and makes marginal contact that does not affect his ability to defend the shot.

Simmons (PHI) falls to the floor and makes marginal contact with Grant as they each attempt to establish control of the loose ball. Grant establishes full control of the ball without being tied up and the timeout is correctly awarded to OKC.
Grant (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in Simmons' (PHI) path and does not deliver the contact.
Harris (PHI) initiates body contact with Westbrook (OKC) and causes him to fall to the floor after his gather.
Schroder (OKC) and Redick (PHI) engage and disengage without affecting the other's ability to freely move.
Ferguson (OKC) legally contests Butler's (PHI) jump shot attempt.
Westbrook (OKC) cleanly dislodges Simmons (PHI) of the ball after he secures the rebound.
RAR shows Morris (OKC) wraps Redick (PHI) during the inbound.
Schroder (OKC) and Scott (PHI) engage and disengage during the inbound without affecting the other's ability to freely move.
Westbrook (OKC) commits the take foul on Scott (PHI).
MOB shows Schroder (OKC) makes contact with Redick's (PHI) arm as he attempts to get to the pass.
